headline: GE (NYSE:GE) Margin Expansion Reinforces Bullish Narratives Despite Slower Growth Forecast
summary: General Electric (GE) reported earnings that highlight continued momentum, with net profit margins rising to 18.3% from 15.8% last year and annual earnings growth accelerating to 36.1%, outpacing its five-year average growth of 32.5%. Both earnings and revenue are forecast to expand at annual rates of 6.7% and 6.6% respectively, which is slower than the broader US market, while shares recently traded at $306.63. Robust profit growth and margin gains paint a picture of high-quality...
